result.adr_address: 18 Gilman's Bazaar, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Affinity Kitchen

reviews.text: Delicious western dishes at good prices in the downtown central office area

Very proper Singaporean style curry laksa here with a variety of condiments such as blood cockles, tofu, meat balls, etc. Taste was pretty close to the stuff back home albeit you'll need get there early to beat the lunch crowd.
Pretty decent laksa. Meat quality is subpar though.

Serve really good laksa but service is really really poor....
Anyway,  pls enjoy the food and don't expect any service,  u will feel much much better~ LOL

By Hong Kong standards good laksa.  Menu attached so you can see the offerings.  If you want to eat in go pre 12 or around 1 or you will have to wait.  Cash or octopus to pay.  Takeaway is quick so convenient even at peak times.
